.TH diodexp 8 "@META_DATE@" "@META_ALIAS@" "@META_NAME@"
.SH NAME
diodexp \- list diod exports
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdiodexp\fR \fI[OPTIONS] host\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B diodexp
lists file systems exported by the distributed I/O daemon, which is an I/O
forwarding service for Linux clusters.
.LP
In addition, \fBdiodexp\fR can be used to implement an \fBautofs\fR program
map for purposes of making \fBdiod\fR mounts available on demand with
minimal client configuration.  See the example map: /etc/auto.g.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I "-a, --auto-direct"
List exports in a format that can be redirected to create an
\fBautofs\fR direct map file.
.TP
.I "-i, --auto-indirect MAP"
List exports in a format that can be redirected to create an
\fBautofs\fR indirect map file for MAP.  File systems with an
initial directory component that does not match MAP are ignored.
.TP
.I "-k, --auto-key KEY"
Used in combination with \fI-a\fR or \fI-i\fR to generate only
the map entry for KEY.  \fBdiodexp\fR can be called with these options
from an executable program map.
.TP
.I "-K, --auto-listkeys"
Used in combination with \fI-a\fR or \fI-i\fR to list available keys.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
diod (8),
diodctl (8),
diodctl.conf (5)
